This is the "Golden Loop" of mobile game marketing. You aren't lying to yourself‚Äîthis is exactly how the most profitable gaming sites in the world operate in 2025.
By combining Playable Ads (short-term pay) with CPA/CPE Offers (long-term pay), you create a "Money Machine" where you get paid at every single stage of the user's journey.
The "GameBridge" 3-Step Money Loop
Here is the honest breakdown of how you get paid in ZAR at each step:
Step 1: The "Test Drive" (CPM Payout)
 * The Action: User clicks "Test FIFA" on your site. A 30-second mini-game starts (they play a penalty shootout, etc.).
 * The Payday: You get paid for the Impression or Engagement.
 * The Reality: Payouts here are small (around R0.10 to R0.50 per play). It doesn't sound like much, but if 1,000 people "test" the game, you've made R500 without anyone even downloading anything.
 * Best Networks for this: Unity Ads or AppLovin. They provide the "Playable" units that you can embed in your site.
Step 2: The "Install" (CPI Payout)
 * The Action: After the 30 seconds, a screen pops up: "Ready for the full game? Download now!" The user clicks and installs it from the Play Store.
 * The Payday: You get a Cost Per Install (CPI) commission.
 * The Reality: In South Africa, a FIFA install typically pays between R5.00 and R15.00.
 * Note: You get this money the moment they open the app for the first time.
Step 3: The "Deep Goal" (CPE Payout)
 * The Action: The user actually likes the game and plays it. They reach a milestone like "Team OVR 85" or "Level 10."
 * The Payday: This is the Cost Per Engagement (CPE) jackpot.
 * The Reality: This is where the big money is. A single South African user reaching a high level can earn you $10 to $20 (R185 - R370).
Total Potential from ONE User:
If one lucky user goes through the whole loop:
 * R0.50 (for the test)
 * R10.00 (for the install)
 * R250.00 (for reaching the level)
 * TOTAL: R260.50 from one person.
How to set this up (The Tech Stack)
To make Step 2 and Step 3 work together, you need an Offerwall Network that supports "Multi-Reward" offers.
 * Sign up for RevU or Torox: These are the best for beginners. They have "Multi-step" offers for games like FIFA and Candy Crush already built-in.
 * Use an "Interstitial" Ad: Use a network like Adsterra or Unity to show the "Playable Ad" before the user gets to your Offerwall link.
 * The "Bridge" Page: * Button 1: "Play 30s Demo" (Triggers the Ad).
   * Button 2: "Download & Earn Rewards" (Triggers your Offerwall Link).
Is there a catch?
The only catch is Traffic. To make R10,000 a month, you need a lot of people clicking "Test."
 * TikTok is your best friend here. Post a video of you playing FIFA and say: "Don't waste 2GB of data, test the game on my site first to see if it's worth it." * South Africans will love this because data is so expensive. You are saving them money while they make you money.
